    <note>Zhang(1) Shao [7163] Qi's [182] and Tan's [3162] brother. Tang(2) Zhun's [7347] father-in-law. Daughter betrothed to Shen(2) Xun [7325], but she died before marriage. His sons held fiscal office: Xiaozeng [3145] was Hubei tiju between 1193 and Fujian yunfu in 1199; Xiaozhong(2) [3143] was dismissed as Jingxi yunpan in 1208. Tan's son, Xiaozhong [3142]), was dismissed as Huainan yunpan in 1209. Zhou Bida, WJ, 65.5b; Guangdong TZ, 16.3b; Lou Yue, WJ, 36.7b; SHY:ZG, 74.33a, 30b, 31a, 75.6b-7a. CBD, 3, 2242-43.</note>
